SIMPLE: windfall
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Windfall
<hw>Wind"fall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Anything blown down or off by the wind, as fruit from a tree, or
the tree itself, or a portion of a forest prostrated by a violent wind,
etc.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧They became a <xex>windfall</xex> upon the
sudden.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An unexpected legacy, or other gain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had a mighty <qex>windfall</qex> out of doubt.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- windfall profits. profits obtained due to a chance ot
unanticipated event that causes an asset to increase unexpectedly in
value. In contrast to profits earned as the normal and expected yield of
an enterprise. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windfallen</ent>⟦br⟧
